scenes.title: The Yellow Stretch
scenes.content:
This model defines a linear map that I call the "yellow stretch".  The map is defined as follows.  First, manually construct the result of applying the map to the XYZ coordinates (modeled as short blue struts).  The desired map, in this case, takes those three short blues into the three green struts shown.

Next, select the three greens in "right-handed" order: counter-clockwise around the yellow axis.  Finally, hit the "+" button in the tools pane, and choose "linear map".  I've done those steps already, in this document.
